main event: A civilian observer noticed a bright orange colored object in the southwest sky. A cigar-shaped object also appeared to go from east to west during the observation.
interesting points: The observer believed they heard a humming sound during the observation.
The object appeared to split and disappear.
The object passed over some clouds during the observation.
The object was described as a bright orange color.
The observer estimated the object was approximately 50 miles away.
sighted object: A bright orange colored object, and a cigar-shaped object
